The Music School of Bitola or Muzicko Uciliste Bitola is a state school that is located in Bitola, Republic of Macedonia.
It provides a full education which includes solfege, music theory, and music history, Every year produces some of the best musicians such as Tose Proeski, Marijan Stojanovski, Lambe Alabakoski, Karolina Goceva, Dimitar Andonovski and Hristijan Spirovski.
The school received a donation from the American government and constructed all buildings, especially at the Primary school for music.
